{"title": "New perspectives in cell adhesion: RGD and integrins", "url": "https://science.sciencemag.org/content/238/4826/491.short", "author": "E Ruoslahti and MD Pierschbacher", "abstract": "Rapid progress has been made in the understanding of the molecular interactions that result in cell adhesion. Many adhesive proteins present in extracellular matrices and in the blood contain the tripeptide arginine-glycine-aspartic acid (RGD) as their cell recognition site \u2026"}